The cadence issue is real: `updateStep()` ends with `collider->storePosition()` at 
`CollisionWorld.cpp:921`, and the H1 loop calls `updateSegment()` repeatedly. That means each 
substep becomes the next substep’s “last position,” which is good for limiting rewind magnitude, but 
it also changes the frame-internal notification/cell cadence from one collision update to N.
