codex
On Q3, the arithmetic is not optional. `FloorMesh` writes hit times into `FloorLocator` as 
normalized time for the delta it was given, and `CollisionResolve` later uses that same normalized 
value to compute a point on the original `MoveSegment`. If H2 loops smaller deltas but leaves 
`result.getTime()` local to a substep, the resolver will rewind/replay at the wrong place.
