codex
H1 and H2 now look like different products. H1 is a physically smaller collision frame, including 
extents and per-segment footprint updates. H2 is a floor-contact query shim inside a full-frame 
resolver, so it must be proven against mixed floor/extent contact ordering and against the fact that 
footprint contacts are still only rebuilt once.
